EmailTemplate.subject: Invitation: Junior School Information Evening and Twilight Tour - 2 April, 2014
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Lead.FirstName}
I'd like to invite you along to our upcoming Junior School Information Evening and Twilight Tour. It's a fantastic opportunity for you to visit St Andrew's Cathedral School, meet our Head of Junior School, Mrs Rhonda Robson and Junior School staff and discover the uniqueness of our vibrant city school. Details are in the attached invitation.
There will also be a supervised crèche available on the evening.
Bookings are essential. Please book your place via our website at www.sacs.nsw.edu.au
I look forward to welcoming you on the day.
Regards
Bruce Perry
Registrar
_______________________________________________________
Junior School Information Evening and Twilight Tour
Visit our vibrant Junior School!
See a school different to anything you've imagined - in the heart of the city, an exciting place where every learner is engaged and growing every day. Our vibrant Junior School offers:
Small class sizes; Extension classes; A strong focus on numeracy and literacy; High expectations for all students; Specialist teachers in language, drama, music, art, sport; Extensive cocurricular opportunities; Supportive learning environment where every child matters.
Wednesday 2 April
6:30pm to 8:00pm
St Andrew's House, Sydney Square, Sydney
The tour commences at 6:30pm with a Twilight Tour of our school facilities, followed by a light supper at 7:00pm. At 7:15pm there will be an information session with our Head of Junior School, Mrs Rhonda Robson and Junior School staff.
Bookings are essential: www.sacs.nsw.edu.au
Bruce Perry Registrar/Mathematics Teacher
St Andrew's Cathedral School
